### Feature Description

It would be nice if there was a utility API for button colors that could be used both internally and by external clients.

[For example the Fab button](https://github.com/angular/components/blob/main/src/material/button/_fab-theme.scss) defines a `_fab-variant` mixin like this:

```
@mixin _fab-variant($foreground, $background) {
  @include mdc-fab-theme.theme((
    container-color: $background,
    icon-color: $foreground,
  ));

  --mat-mdc-fab-color: #{$foreground};
}
```

We can't use this outside of Angular because its private.

Something like this can be used both within the current code base and as a client facing API for extending the Fab button colors:

```
@mixin fab-variant($color-class, $foreground, $background) {
  &.#{ $color-class } {
    @include mdc-fab-theme.theme(
      (
        container-color: $background,
        icon-color: $foreground,
      )
    );
    background-color: var(--mdc-fab-container-color, transparent);
    color: var(--mdc-fab-icon-color, inherit);
  }
}
```
It can be called like this with color extensions for the Fab button.

```
  .mat-mdc-fab {
    @include fab-variant(mat-success, $on-success, $success);
    @include fab-variant(mat-danger, $on-danger, $danger);
    @include fab-variant(mat-info, $on-info, $info);
  }
```

Also `_mdc-helpers` is also private.  Angular uses it in conjunction with delegation to the Material Components Web API like this:

```
@include mdc-helpers.using-mdc-theme($config) { ...
```

So it would be nice to be able to follow the same approach for grabbing property values via the `mdc` API ... 


### Use Case

Extend buttons colors.
